012}}</ref>\n| 27\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Canada|artist=Eurythmics|title=Touch|award=Platinum|number=2|type=album|relyear=1983|certyear=1984|date=1 June 1984|accessdate=16 October 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|artist=Eurythmics|title=Touch|award=Gold|type=album|relyear=1983|certyear=1991}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Netherlands|artist=Eurythmics|title=Touch|award=Gold|type=album|relyear=1983|certyear=1984|accessdate=9 February 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|artist=Eurythmics|title=Touch|award=Platinum|type=album|recent=website|id=3087|relyear=1983|date=4 March 1984|accessdate=16 October 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|artist=Eurythmics|title=Touch|award=Platinum|type=album|relyear=1983|certyear=1984|refname=\"BPI\"}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|artist=Eurythmics|title=Touch|award=Platinum|type=album|relyear=1983|certyear=1984|date=4 October 1984|refname=\"RIAA\"}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=yes}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Eurythmics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Touch (Eurythmics Album)}}\n[[Category:1983 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by David A. Stewart]]\n[[Category:Eurythmics albums]]\n[[Category:RCA Records albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2011}}\n{{italic title}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Touch\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Eurythmics]]\n| cover      = Eurythmics - Touch.png\n| border     = yes\n| released   = {{start date|1983|11|14|df=yes}}\n| recorded   = Summer 1983\n| studio     = [[The Church Studios|The Church]], London\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Synth-pop]]<ref name=\"rs500\"/>|[[New wave music|new wave]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Besenyodi |first=Adam |url=https://www.popmatters.com/051205-eurythmics-2496104064.html |title=This Is What the Future Sounded Like |work=[[PopMatters]] |date=4 December 2005 |accessdate=16 October 2018 |quote=...''Touch'' kept them on new wave's cutting-edge.}}</ref>}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=45|s=30}}\n| label      = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| producer   = [[David A. Stewart]]\n| prev_title = [[Sweet Dreams (Are Made of This) (album)|Sweet Dreams (Are Made of This)]]\n| prev_year  = 1983\n| next_title = [[Touch Dance]]\n| next_year  = 1984\n| misc       = {{Singles\n  | name        = Touch\n  | type        = studio\n  | single1     = [[Who's That Girl? (Eurythmics song)|Who's That Girl?]]\n  | single1date = June 1983\n  | single2     = [[Right by Your Side]]\n  | single2date = October 1983\n  | single3     = [[Here Comes the Rain Again]]\n  | single3date = January 1984\n  }}\n}}\n{{album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Promis |first=Jose F. |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/touch-mw0000189822 |title=Touch \u2013 Eurythmics |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=12 August 2011}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Encyclopedia of Popular Music]]''\n| rev2score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite book |last=Larkin |first=Colin |authorlink=Colin Larkin (writer) |title=[[Encyclopedia of Popular Music|The Encyclopedia of Popular Music]] |edition=5th concise |publisher=[[Omnibus Press]] |year=2011 |isbn=0-85712-595-8}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]''\n| rev3score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Eurythmics: Touch |magazine=[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]] |issue= |date= |page=134 |issn=1351-0193 |quote=Recorded in a frantic three-week burst of inspiration, the third Eurythmics album saw Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart raising their game significantly.}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Connelly |first=Christopher |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/artists/eurythmics/albums/album/98934/review/5941829/touch |title=Eurythmics: Touch |work=Rolling Stone |date=2 February 1984 |accessdate=4 June 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070713021447/http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/eurythmics/albums/album/98934/review/5941829/touch |archivedate=13 July 2007}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Rolling Stone Album Guide]]''\n| rev5Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite book |last=Considine |first=J. D. |authorlink=J. D. Considine |chapter=Eurythmics |editor1-last=Brackett |editor1-first=Nathan |editor1-link=Nathan Brackett |editor2-last=Hoard |editor2-first=Christian |editor2-link=Christian Hoard |title=[[The Rolling Stone Album Guide|The New Rolling Stone Album Guide]] |publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]] |edition=4th |year=2004 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/newrollingstonea00brac/page/283 283\u201384] |isbn=0-7432-0169-8 }}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Smash Hits]]''\n| rev6Score = 9/10<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Anthony |first=Lisa |title=Eurythmics: Touch |magazine=[[Smash Hits]] |volume=5 |issue=24 |date=24 November \u2013 7 December 1983 |page=27 |issn=0260-3004}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[The Village Voice]]''\n| rev7Score = B<ref>{{cite news |last=Christgau |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Christgau |url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/xg/cg/cgv5-84.php |title=Christgau's Consumer Guide |work=[[The Village Voice]] |date=29 May 1984 |accessdate=4 June 2016 |via=RobertChristgau.com}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Touch''''' is the third studio album by the British [[New wave music|new wave]] duo [[Eurythmics]]. It was released on 14 November 1983 by [[RCA Records]]. ''Touch'' became the duo's first number-one album on the [[UK Albums Chart]], and also reached the top 10 of the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. It has since been certified Platinum in both the United Kingdom and the United States.<ref name=\"BPI\"/><ref name=\"RIAA\"/> The album spawned the singles \"[[Who's That Girl? (Eurythmics song)|Who's That Girl?]]\", \"[[Right by Your Side]]\" and \"[[Here Comes the Rain Again]]\".\n\nThe album was listed on ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s [[Rolling Stone's 500 Greatest Albums of All Time|The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time]] in 2003, and again on a revised list in 2012.<ref name=\"rs500\"/>\n\n==Background==\nBy the time ''Touch'' was released, Eurythmics had achieved international success with their commercially successful single \"[[Sweet Dreams (Are Made of This)]]\" and their [[Sweet Dreams (Are Made of This) (album)|album of the same name]]. Preceded by the single \"[[Who's That Girl? (Eurythmics song)|Who's That Girl?]]\", ''Touch'' was recorded and mixed in about three weeks at Eurythmics' own London studio facility, The Church.\n\nAn accompanying remix EP, ''[[Touch Dance]]'', was released in May 1984.\n\n===2005 re-release===\nOn 14 November 2005, [[Sony BMG]] repackaged and released Eurythmics' back catalogue as \"2005 Deluxe Edition Reissues\". Each of their eight studio albums' original track listings were supplemented with bonus tracks and remixes.\n\n===Accolades===\nIn 2000 it was voted number 221 in [[Colin Larkin]]'s ''[[All Time Top 1000 Albums]]''.<ref name=\"Larkin\">{{cite book|title=[[All Time Top 1000 Albums]]|author=[[Colin Larkin]]|publisher=[[Virgin Books]]|date=2000|edition=3rd|isbn=0-7535-0493-6}}</ref>In 2012, the album was ranked number 492 on ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine's list of [[Rolling Stone's 500 Greatest Albums of All Time|the 500 greatest albums of all time]].<ref name=\"rs500\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/500-greatest-albums-of-all-time-156826/eurythmics-touch-47932/ |title=500 Greatest Albums of All Time |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=31 May 2012 |accessdate=16 October 2018}}</ref> It had originally appeared at number 500 on the 2003 version of the list. ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' placed the album at number 47 on its list of the \"Best Albums of the 1980s\".<ref>[http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/feature/best-albums-of-the-1980s/308/page_6 Slant Magazine]</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = [[Annie Lennox]] and [[David A. Stewart]], except where noted\n| total_length = 45:30\n| title1 = 