allow and the deep, long-range ecology movement: A summary |journal=[[Inquiry: An Interdisciplinary Journal of Philosophy]] |volume=16 |issue=1 |pages=95\u2013100 |doi= |url=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Devall & Sessions 1985\">{{cite book |first1=Bill|last1=Devall|first2=George|last2= Sessions|author-link= |date=1985 |title=Deep Ecology: Living as if Nature Mattered |url= |publisher=[[Gibbs Smith]] |location=UT, U.S. |page= |isbn=978-0879052478}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Tucker & Grim 2019\">{{cite journal |first1=Mary Evelyn |last1=Tucker |author-link1=Mary Evelyn Tucker |first2=John |last2=Grim |date=Winter 2019 |title=Thomas Berry and the Rights of Nature (excerpted from the book Thomas Berry: A Biography) |journal=KOSMOS Journal for Global Transformation |volume= |issue= |pages= |doi= |url=https://www.kosmosjournal.org/kj_article/thomas-berry-and-the-rights-of-nature/ |access-date=2020-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408224656/https://www.kosmosjournal.org/kj_article/thomas-berry-and-the-rights-of-nature/ |archive-date=2020-04-08 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Millennium Ecosystem Assessment 2005\">{{cite report |author= |author-link= |authors= |date= |title=Millennium Ecosystem Assessment, Ecosystems and Human Well-Being: Our Human Planet |url=https://www.millenniumassessment.org/en/Global.html |publisher=[[Island Press]] |location=Washington, DC, U.S. |page= |docket= |access-date= |quote= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007043940/http://www.millenniumassessment.org/en/Global.html |archivedate=2019-10-07 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Cullinan 2010\">{{cite web |url=https://therightsofnature.org/wp-content/uploads/pdfs/Legal-Case-for-Universal-Declaration-Cormac-Cullinan.pdf |title=The Legal Case for a Universal Declaration of the Rights of Mother Earth |first=Cormac |last=Cullinan |author-link=Cormac Cullinan |date=2010 |website=therightsofnature.org |publisher= |access-date= |quote= |archive-url=https://web.archiv