|last1= Sikkink|author-link1= Kathryn Sikkink|first2= Hun Joon|last2= Kim|date= |title= The Justice Cascade: The Origins and Effectiveness of Prosecutions of Human Rights Violations|journal= Annual Review of Law and Social Science|volume= 9|issue= |pages= 269-285|doi= |url= https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/pdf/10.1146/annurev-lawsocsci-102612-133956|access-date= 2020-04-20|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200411190000/https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/pdf/10.1146/annurev-lawsocsci-102612-133956|archive-date= 2020-04-11|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Kauffman 2020\">{{cite report |first= Craig M.|last= Kauffman|date=April 2020 |title=Mapping Transnational Rights of Nature Networks & Laws: New Global Governance Structures for More Sustainable Development |url=http://files.harmonywithnatureun.org/uploads/upload924.pdf |publisher=Harmony with Nature, United Nations |page= |docket= |access-date= |quote= }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Anthony 2017\">{{cite book |first=Carl |last= Anthony|author-link=Carl Anthony |date=2017 |title=The Earth, the City, and the Hidden Narrative of Race |url= |publisher=[[New Village Press]] |location=U.S. |page= |isbn=978-1613320211}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Kauffman & Martin 2019\">{{cite journal |first1=Craig M. |last1=Kauffman |first2=Pamela L. |last2=Martin |date=Winter 2019 |title=How Courts Are Developing River Rights Jurisprudence: Comparing Guardianship in New Zealand, Colombia, and India |journal=[[Vermont Law School|Vermont]] Journal of Environmental Law |volume=20 |issue=3 |pages= |doi= |url=http://vjel.vermontlaw.edu/files/2020/04/VJEL_20_3.pdf}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Grim & Tucker 2014\">{{cite book |first1=John|last1=Grim|first2=Mary Evelyn |last2=Tucker|author-link2=Mary Evelyn Tucker|date= |title=Ecology and Religion|url= |publisher=[[Island Press]]|location=U.S. |page=2014 |isbn=978-1597267083}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"UDHR 1948\">{{citation|title=Universal Declaration of Human Rights|year=1948|publisher=United Nations