 2019\">{{cite book |first=Michelle |last= Lim|author-link= |date=2019 |title=Charting Environmental Law Futures in the Anthropocene |url= |publisher=[[Springer Nature]] |location= |page= |isbn=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Perkins 2017\">{{cite news |first=Madeleine |last=Perkins |date=July 9, 2017 |title=How Pittsburgh embraced a radical environmental movement popping up in conservative towns across America |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/rights-for-nature-preventing-fracking-pittsburgh-pennsylvania-2017-7 |work=[[Business Insider]] |location= |access-date= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411154426/https://www.businessinsider.com/rights-for-nature-preventing-fracking-pittsburgh-pennsylvania-2017-7 |archive-date=April 11, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Gaia Foundation 2019\">{{cite web |author=[[Gaia Foundation]] |title=Rights of Nature Gain Ground in Uganda\u2019s Legal System |url=https://www.gaiafoundation.org/rights-of-nature-gain-ground-in-ugandas-legal-system/ |date=February 2019 |website= |publisher=Gaia Foundation |location=U.K. |access-date= |quote= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200116220941/https://www.gaiafoundation.org/rights-of-nature-gain-ground-in-ugandas-legal-system/ |archive-date=2020-01-16 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Kauffman & Martin 2017\">{{cite journal |first1=Craig M. |last1=Kauffman |first2=Pamela L. |last2=Martin |date=April 2017 |title=Can Rights of Nature Make Development More Sustainable? Why Some Ecuadorian Lawsuits Succeed and Others Fail |journal=[[World Development (journal)|World Development]] |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |volume=92 |issue= |pages=130-142 |doi=10.1016/j.worlddev.2016.11.017 |url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0305750X16305496 |access-date=2020-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411234120/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0305750X16305496 |archive-date=2020-04-11 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Schaefer 2018\">{{cite journal |first1=Stacy Jane |last1=Schaefer |date=April 18, 2018 |title=he Standing of Nature: The Delineated Natural Ecosystem Proxy |journal=George Washington Journal of Energy and Environmental Law |volume=9 |issue=2 |pages= |doi= |url=https://gwjeel.com/2018/04/18/the-standing-of-nature-the-delineated-natural-ecosystem-proxy/ |access-date=April 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411234121/https://gwjeel.com/2018/04/18/the-standing-of-nature-the-delineated-natural-ecosystem-proxy/ |archive-date=April 11, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Binjaku & Dixit 2019\">{{cite thesis |first1=Xhulio |last1= Binjaku|first2=Milap |last2=Dixit |date=2019 |title=Other Equators: measures for an international tribunal for the Rights of Nature |type= |chapter= |publisher=[[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]], Dept of Architecture |docket= |oclc= |url=http://oastats.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/122518 |access-date=}}</ref>\n\n\n<ref name=\"Iorns Magallanes 2015\">{{cite journal |first1=Catherine J. |last1= Iorns Magallanes |date=2015 |title=Maori Cultural Rights in Aotearoa New Zealand: Protecting the Cosmology that Protects the Environment (Victoria University of Wellington Legal Research Paper No. 6/2016) |journal=[[Widener Law Review]]|publisher= |volume=21 |issue=1 |pages=273-327 |doi= |url=https://ssrn.com/abstract=2677396}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Cheng 2017\">{{cite news |first=Derek |last=Cheng |date=December 21, 2017 |title=Mt Taranaki will be granted special legal status similar to Te Urewera and the Whanganui River |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=11963982 |work=[[New Zealand Herald]] |location= |access-date= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108203949/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=11963982 |archive-date=November 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n\n<ref name=\"Roy 2017\">{{cite news |first=Eleanor Ainge |last=Roy |date=December 22, 2017 |title=N