riter. He was born in [[Fort de Kock]], [[Dutch East Indies]] (now Bukittinggi, Indonesia) in 1898.{{sfn|Eneste|2001|p=203}} He finished his education in various cities, including Batavia (now [[Jakarta]]), [[Bandung]], [[Padang]], and [[Medan]].{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Rustam Sutan Palindih}} In the 1920s and 30s Rustam held a variety of jobs, including as the owner of a small shop and a farmer. He eventually became involved with the journalistic and literary industries, working at [[Balai Pustaka]] and heading the newspaper ''Harian Neratja''.{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Rustam Sutan Palindih}} From 1933 until 1938 he was a member of a [[native Indonesian|native]] political council, vocally opposing the Dutch colonial presence in the Indies.{{sfn|Abdullah|2009|p=96}}\n\nRustam began his involvement with the local film industry during the 1940s, writing novelisations of films by [[Tan Tjoei Hock]] and Soeska.{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Rustam Sutan Palindih}}{{sfn|WorldCat, Rustam Sutan Palindih}} After the [[Empire of Japan]] [[Japanese occupation of Indonesia|occupied the Indies]] beginning in 1942, he collaborated with the Japanese forces in making the short [[Japanese propaganda during World War II|propaganda films]] ''Di Desa'' and ''Di Menara'' for the studio Nippon Eigasha.{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Filmography}}{{sfn|Biran|2009|pp=319, 332}} During the [[Indonesian National Revolution]] (1945\u20131949) that followed the occupation Rustam directed his only feature film, ''[[Air Mata Mengalir di Tjitarum]]'' (''Tears Flow in Tjitarum''), in 1948, which was the feature film debut of [[Sofia WD]].{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Filmography}}{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Air Mata Mengalir}} His last work in the film industry, a script entitled ''Terang Bulan'' (''Full Moon''), was filmed in 1950 and directed by Mustadjab. Starring Sofia and [[Rd Mochtar]], the production followed two lovers separated by crime, war, and family who are ultimately able to reunite.{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Air Mata Mengalir}}\n\nBy the 1950s, after Indonesia's independence was recognised, Rustam had become mostly a literary documentarian, although he continued to publish some works on the subject.{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Rustam Sutan Palindih}} He also wrote on the nation's politics and recorded a version of the folktale [[Lutung Kasarung]].{{sfn|WorldCat, Rustam Sutan Palindih}} He died in 1971 after several years of ill health.{{sfn|Eneste|2001|p=203}}\n\n==Filmography==\nPalindih directed two short propaganda films and one feature film. He wrote a total of four films:{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Roestam St Palindih}}{{sfn|Filmindonesia.or.id, Filmography}}\n*''Di Desa'' (''In the Village''; 1943; short film)&nbsp;\u2013 Director and screenwriter\n*''Di Menara'' (''In the Tower''; 1943; short film)&nbsp;\u2013 Director and screenwriter\n*''[[Air Mata Mengalir di Tjitarum]]'' (''Tears Flow in Tjitarum''; 1948)&nbsp;\u2013 Director and screenwriter\n*''Terang Bulan'' (''Full Moon''; 1950)&nbsp;\u2013 Story\n\n==References==\n'''Footnotes'''\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n'''Bibliography'''\n{{refbegin|40em}}\n*{{cite book\n |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c39TDpLki8wC\n |title=Indonesia: Towards Democracy\n |isbn=978-981-230-366-0\n |author1=Abdullah\n |first1=Taufik\n |year=2009\n |ref=harv\n |publisher=Institute of Southeast Asian Studies\n |location=Singapore\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | title = Air Mata Mengalir di Tjitarum\n  | language = Indonesian\n  | url = http://filmindonesia.or.id/movie/title/lf-a025-48-840416_air-mata-mengalir-di-tjitarum\n  | work = filmindonesia.or.id\n  | publisher = Konfidan Foundation\n  | location = Jakarta\n  | accessdate = 23 August 2012\n  | archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/6A7ge4yir\n  | archivedate = 23 August 2012\n  | ref = {{sfnRef|Filmindonesia.or.id, Air Mata Mengalir}}\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | title = [[Sejarah Film 1900\u20131950: Bikin Film di Jawa]]\n  |trans-title=History of Film 1900\u20131950: Makin